items.title: Hell to Pay [Outlaws of Thunder Junction]
items.body_html:
Set: Outlaws of Thunder Junction
Type: Sorcery
Rarity: Rare
Cost: {X}{R}
Hell to Pay deals X damage to target creature. Create a number of tapped Treasure tokens equal to the amount of excess damage dealt to that creature this way.
For years afterward, lucky explorers who found the cave could chip gold fragments off the rocky walls.

items.title: Oko, the Ringleader [Outlaws of Thunder Junction]
items.body_html:
Set: Outlaws of Thunder Junction
Type: Legendary Planeswalker — Oko
Rarity: Mythic
Cost: {2}{G}{U}
At the beginning of combat on your turn, Oko, the Ringleader becomes a copy of up to one target creature you control until end of turn, except he has hexproof.
+1: Draw two cards. If you've committed a crime this turn, discard a card. Otherwise, discard two cards.
−1: Create a 3/3 green Elk creature token.
−5: For each other nonland permanent you control, create a token that's a copy of that permanent.

items.title: Nexus of Becoming [Outlaws of Thunder Junction: The Big Score]
items.body_html:
Set: Outlaws of Thunder Junction: The Big Score
Type: Artifact
Rarity: Mythic
Cost: {6}
At the beginning of combat on your turn, draw a card. Then you may exile an artifact or creature card from your hand. If you do, create a token that's a copy of the exiled card, except it's a 3/3 Golem artifact creature in addition to its other types.
